\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Virtual Reality (VR) has transformed traditional learning methodologies by providing immersive experiences. VR applications in education range from virtual field trips to complex surgery simulations in medical schools. It involves technologies such as head-mounted displays (HMD), motion tracking, and 3D environments to create interactive learning experiences. Benefits of VR in education include enhanced engagement, improved retention rates, and the ability to simulate complex or hazardous scenarios safely. As VR technology advances, it is increasingly adopted in schools and universities, offering students experiences that are otherwise not possible in a traditional classroom.}